                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I wasn't convinced we needed dot crits until I started raiding planes recently.  I was always amazed I could do 10k damage on one mob if he lasted 2 or more minutes.<br />Then I started to see how pitiful 10k is comepared to nukers. Ouch. They out damage me in like 3 or 4 casts!<br /><br />So ok I'm convinced...dot crit aa is needed.<br /><br />But how would it work?<br /><br />Some people are in favor or a percentage chance that the entire dot will crit.<br /><br />Personally I favor a percentage chance for a crit on each tick.<br /><br />Or even better I'd like a fixed percentage (maybe 10%?) at lvl 1 and with the next 2 levels you buy the crit tick from double to triple to quadruple.<br /><br />So with one aa in dot crit a typical dot might look like this:<br /><br />100 100 100 100 200 100 100 100 200 100 100 100<br /><br />At lvl 2 it would be like this (dot crit does triple base on the crit tick)<br /><br />100 100 100 100 300 100 100 100 300 100 100 100<br /><br />And lvl 3 it would do this:<br /><br />100 100 100 100 400 100 100 100 400 100 100 100<br /><br /><br />Of course the example is based on 100 per tick dot.<br /><br />Damage from spells like funeral pyre and BoT would be pretty darned impressive to say the least!<br /><br />Could also have a lvl requirement like 59 for lvl 1, 62 for lvl 2 and 64 for lvl 3 or something like that.</span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
