                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> finally some good stuff on this idea.. when i read this last night i agreed with what Usal said even before he said it, and even said it out loud pretty much the same way when i read an earlier post above his. <br /><br />after thinking about it though, the only problem i see is that a lot of nukes (most?) have a chance to do partial damage. dots never do partial damage. ok, with BA there's a variable amount to add to the base damage, but the base damage is Always the same. therefore in this scenario we are always doubling the damage of our dots full potential (plus additional BA damage) on a crit, something a nuker could never do. i don't know what the solution to this is, matter of fact i just saw the problem. off the top of my head a possible solution might be to make the *crit* damage variable, because we don't have (and don't want...) variable base damage on our dots.<br /><br />for example, a saryrn's kiss for, say, with baIV, 210 damage per tic could do a variable amount of damage *up to and including* double the amount of 420 each and every tic, or it could do as low as &lt;insert reasonable percentage of the base here&gt; damage. /shrug hadn't thought this out, again, just off the top of my head. if you look two paragraphs down and agree that we'll never get what is proposed there (at least in the foreseeable future), then, maybe that is part of our justication for wanting double damage each and every time we crit. <br /><br />and if you're (which i like btw) going to use the comparison of us to wizards, with wiz being the master of nuke, and us being the master of dot (err what else are we? and don't tell me master of the dead..maybe master of solo  : ) but that doesn't fit into the whole Vision now does it? then again, who really knows what the Vision is nowadays), then the innate chance to crit makes perfect sense and i agreed with the thought when i read it elsewhere before too.<br /><br />the point that was made in favor of cold dots is something that isn't new to my thinking either, and i agree with. well, and it goes in line with the whole 'wizard of dots' way of thinking. more Magic dots would be completely reasonable too. and the statement made about a mob that is poison and fire resistant completely ruining our dps is right on. i'd even go a step further and say if *either* of those two are resisted we're severely handicapped, as far as highish dps goes. so what does that leave us with? cold (nothing) magic (SK mainly, add ToM in if you're desperate yeah yeah and splurt, but we're talking dps and dps without needing 12 spell slots,), disease...slowwww. and as was also said, we have to *stack* this stuff.. we can't just chain dot the same dot that works because it's the biggest hitter in our lineup that isn't resisted.. /chuckle. so giving us a wider variety of save vs. dots seems like a good step in the right direction, and inline with the whole dot crit thing which is inline with comparing us to wiz as the wiz of dots.<br /><br />my two coppers.. and if anyone reading these posts doesn't agree with anything else, they have to agree that dots are lagging behind nukes in capability. either that or they haven't been plain embarrassed yet like Bonker was to start this whole thread. <br /><br />and i'm not a whiner or a 'but but but i want what THEY haaave' or a nerf them they are too good at thing 'X' person. i love playing a necro. these seem like really good ideas to help round out our class though.<br /><br />i'm gonna go get a coffee</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
